Database Schema
import { pgTable, text, serial, real, integer } from "drizzle-orm/pg-core";

export const placesTable = pgTable("places", {
  id: serial("id").primaryKey(),
  name: text("name").notNull(),
  direction: text("direction").notNull(),
  rating: real("rating"),
  cost: integer("cost"),
});
Explanation
id
id: serial("id").primaryKey()
Unique identifier.
Auto-incremented.
name
name: text("name").notNull()
Stores the name of the place.

Example:

Goa Beach
Ooty Hills
Mysore Palace
direction
direction: text("direction").notNull()
Stores the location or address.

Example:

North Goa
Mysore, Karnataka
Ooty, Tamil Nadu
rating
rating: real("rating")
Stores decimal ratings.

Example:

4.3
4.7
4.9
cost
cost: integer("cost")
Stores estimated expenditure.

Example:

5000
8000
12000
Backend API
Example:

app.get("/api/places", async (req, res) => {

  const places = await db.select()
                         .from(placesTable);

  res.json(places);

});
Working
Client sends a request.
Express receives the request.
Drizzle ORM queries PostgreSQL.
Data is returned as JSON.
React displays the results.
React Component
function PlaceCard({ place }) {

  return (

    <div className="card">

      <h2>{place.name}</h2>

      <p>{place.direction}</p>

      <p>Rating: {place.rating}</p>

      <p>Cost: ₹{place.cost}</p>

    </div>

  );

}
Sample Output
Goa Beach

Location : North Goa

Rating : 4.8

Estimated Cost : ₹5000
